Definition: a type of oratory used to eulogize or condemn a person or group of people
Example: Pericles' funeral oration for Athenians killed in the Peloponnesian War is a famous example of epideictic oratory
Synonyms: oratory, a, type, of, used, to, eulogize, or, condemn, person, group, people, Pericles, funeral, oration, for, Athenians, killed, in, the, Peloponnesian, War, is, famous, example, epideictic
Category: noun.communication
